  "texts": [
    "On the second day, the sections were incubated with HRP-conjugated secondary antibodies for two hours at RT.",
    "Then the sections were treated with Streptavidin HRP for 10 min and visualized by DAB substrate application (Abcam, Waltham, USA, Cat#ab64238).",
    "The cell nuclei were counterstained with Hematoxylin, then dehydrated and mounted as the hematoxylin and eosin (H&E) staining.",
    "For BrdU staining, the sections were treated with 2 N HCl for 5 min at 37 °C before blocking.",
    "The slides were imaged with Axioscan or Tissue FAXS Plus."
  ],
